DOCUMENT();
loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'PGchoicemacros.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

#define the variables
$x = random(1, 3, .1);
$y = random(1, 3, .1);
$s = random(2, 5);

BEGIN_PGML
A map shows the size of Grand Rapids to be a rectangle [` [$x] cm `] by [` [$y] cm `]. The scale of the map is 1 cm = [` [$s] `] miles.


a) What is the actual size of Grand Rapids? [_]{Real($s*$x)} [` mi  `] by [_]{Real($s*$y)} [` mi  `]

b) What is the map area of Grand Rapids? [_]{Real($x*$y)} [` cm ^2 `]

c) What is the actual area of Grand Rapids? [_]{Real($s**2*$x*$y)} [` mi ^2  `]

END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
a) The actual size of Grand Rapids is found by
[```[$x]\;\text{cm} \cdot \frac{4\;\text{miles}}{1\;\text{cm}} = [@$x*$s@]\;\text{miles}```]
[```[$y]\;\text{cm} \cdot \frac{4\;\text{miles}}{1\;\text{cm}} = [@$y*$s@]\;\text{miles}```]

b) The map area is the product of the two map dimensions or [`A=[@$x*$y@]\;\text{cm}^2`].

c) The actual area is the product of the two actual dimensions or [`A=[@ $s**2*$x*$y@]\;\text{mi}^2`]. 
END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
 